    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-13T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="626"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d626">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/11597: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-13T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 13, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 13—1:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1140. Japanese Consulate General informs me that orders have been issued by
                    Japanese military and naval authorities to stop operations against Hohsien,
                    Anhui. Similar instructions are being conveyed to the Hohsien front by special
                    Japanese plane.<note n="56" xml:id="d626fn56">Colonel Hashimoto at Wuhu
                        similarly assured British representatives that “Hohsien would not be
                        attacked until refugees had been evacuated.” (793.94/11615)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
